betterquesting:10.desc:8: First off you will find that it really hurts your hand if you punch a tree (it is wood i think that would hurt). You may want to find an alternitive, try some Flint tools. Tinkers' tools may have to wait til a little bit later but lets make some basic tools to see if we can collect that wood without breaking our hands. Though you will need to punch a tree first.
Turn some wood into some basic tinkers' tables so we can start with some tools!
Now that you have some stone tools why don't you go get some clay and bone meal so you can make some unfired porcelain to start.

I know by this point you hate me, but at least after this chapter things will get alot better for you, now in true vanilla respect its time to make a furnace... ignore how long it took you to get here.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Time to turn the world molten!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: With your seared furnace made, you have your glass at the ready and its time to work towards a greater smeltery, you will have to make the porcelain versions of most things, then pour molten grout over the top of them to make the seared equivilants
Now that you have some wood going to make patterns make some (insert name of thing to make pattern here) and place it on a drying rack.
Great! Now that we can collect some wood, let's do so. Go chop down some trees so we can make some good flint tools.
Now that you have that basic tinkers tables why dont we get some flint or cobblestone to start your mining process! Remember normal tools above stone arent going to be able to mine things!
Lets make a porcelain smelter and heater to get started into getting some metals!
Now that you are about to make the smeltey you are going to want to make some dust so you can smelt down some ore.

If you are hankering for some more space to put some things while you are adventuring I suggest that you go look backpacks. You might not be able to make the higher versions of the backpacks but it will give you a little more space while you start exploring.
Some ores you will find do not spawn in the over world for starting you will be able to find some Tin ore, Iron ore, Redstone ore, Copper ore, and some certus quartz ore.

While you explore you may find all sorts of things in this world! This world is vast and diverse so we suggest that you explore and look for a nice place to set up shop! But be careful you may find that the monsters in this world can be hard to kill!

Now that we have the smeltery going why don't we make some ingots that we are going to need. Let's start with some copper and iron ingots. Remember the smeltery does not double ores but is currently your only way to process them. If you havent already lava in a normal tinkers smeltery will be needed, heaters at this point will not be sufficient
No Description
Now that we have that Pure Daisy let's make some Living rock and some Living wood. These will be needed for later on.

Let's get some tin to make some better tools so we can keep going towards those harder ores! In order to pour this tin head you will have to make a clay cast to start out with. Though be careful for this cast will only have 1 use to it.
No Description
No Description
No Description

Now that you have obtained an extra melter and an alloy tank you will want to use these to get seared stone, place a melter on either side of the alloy tank with heaters below all 3 and add some clay and compressed sand, and then pour the molten grout over some gravel and you will now have seared stone.
No Description
No Description
No Description
No Description
No Description
No Description
Now that we have some power it's time to get a better way to turn ore into dust. Let's start with a IC2C Macerator.
Now that we have that Petal Apthecary why don't we make a pure daisy. I think this flower will be useful.

Since we have some seared stone why don't we get a coke oven going so we can make some Treated wood! You will probably need that later on. You will also want to keep all the coal coke you gather and you may want to get a lot of coal coke.
Now I bet that casting plates is getting a little tiresome. Let's see if we can find a better way to do it again! Why not try that rolling machine from Railcraft?
Nice you found a way to make plates a little easier! (Don't worry there will be better ways to do this later on.) Now why don't we use some of those plates to start generating power?
Since you have all the mana process made all you need is the mana pool. It's time to make a mana pool meaning that you are going to have to make a carbon plate from IC2.
Your smeltery is serving you well and its time you made some plates, to get started iron and invar seem like a good way to do it, invar can be made in the smeltery
Ouch! That took 4 ingots to make a plate? I bet there is a better way to make some plates. Why not try and make a cast so you can pour them.

Now that you have plates its time to make your journey into everything energy based. I think that a steam dynamo would be a good start for the other power options. Why don't we go make one? You will have to use some coal and a little bit of water to start this thing up. We may find a better way to get some fuel to this thing.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's getting a little steamy in here.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: That solid fuel for that steam dynamo is a little annoying to maintain, isn't it? Why don't we get some steam going into that thing to make it a little better? Before we can do that though, you are going to have to give this thing a little upgrade! To start with lets get it a hardened upgrade kit, then we will have to get it a turbine so that it can use that steam!
Since we have made some Crushed ore why dont we go all the way and wash that to make some better dust to smelt down. So let's go ahead and make an ore washer.
I think that it is time to make a compressor to start getting things compressed down.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Have you ever wanted to be a Bontanist?
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Now we need to start on some Botania. First we are going to need that petal Apothecary. Wow! That takes a bucket? Well good thing we have that plate cast now.
Now that we have the petal apothecary let's start getting some mana going. Why don't we start with a munchdew.
Now that we have a flower getting mana and some living rock and wood lets make a mana spreader to get some mana going into that mana pool that we are going to have.
No Description
6In order to start up the smeltery you will need to make a bucket to grab some lava and fill that seared tank.
Now that you have the Engineer's hammer why not make a blast furnace so that you can make some refined iron and keep progressing towards the nether.

Since we cannot get diamonds in the overworld, the only way to make your pickaxe strong enough will be to get manasteel, but dont get ahead of yourself, you will need carbon plates in order to that point

The nether, much like the overworld, will have specific ores that will only spawn in the nether. primarily you will care about diamond, but there is also ardite ore, cobalt ore and Nether Quartz. Though some of these ores you will not be able to mine at first so keep that in mind as you go explore the nether. Also the mobs that you encounter in the nether may be a little hard to fight than the ones in the overworld so you may want to make some armor before your first exploration.
Now that you have progressed into immersive engineering, let's get that final progression of plates and gears and make the metal press so you can make plates without that hassle of a smeltery
Since you have a coke oven up and running, we should use that creasote that it is making and make some treated wood that will be use in some botania and immersive engineering.

Once you have gone to the nether you will have some nickel and will be able to make the hardened upgrade and the turbine upgrade for the steam generator which will allow you to run the steam dynamo off of steam. However you will need to have something to generate steam for this.

Since we made that generator let's have something that uses that power. Let's start with making the Engineer's manual. Since you already have the engineer's hammer you can make this book and start in on some immersive engineering.

Now that you have gone to the nether, made the plate press, and made some mana pearls, I think that it is time that you can make a Storage scanner so that you can have an easier time of that issue we all have "Storage" and sorting.
You remember that external steam i talked about? well here it is, remember so that you dont have to keep gathering lava, steam can be used as a smeltery fuel
Since we have the engineer's book lets make the Engineer's table so we can start to make components for these multiblocks.
Now that you have started in on the progression of making IC2C machines why don't we make a way that we can store some of that power for later use.
No Description

cNow that we can pump some steam into that steam dynamo that we have upgraded we will have to make a way to fuel it with steam. Why don't we make a steam boiler from railcraft. You will have to make some solid fuel fireboxes and some low pressure boiler tanks. This will be a multiblock structure. You will start with at bottom layer of fireboxes ranging from 1 block to a 3x3. Then you will be able to add low pressure boiler tanks on top of those. The structure will change with however many fireboxes you have with the structure. This will change to a maximum of 1 height on the 1 firebox to a 4 tall on a 3x3 firebox structure. You will later on when you get liquid fuels be able to make a fluid firebox and be able to pump in fuels to run the boiler.
No Description

You begin to realise that your stone tools will not get you far in life and realise that you can make a pickaxe head to mine tin out of compressed sand inside of your melter, these tools can be repaired with a vitrified sharpening kit

Note: compressed sand melts into vitrified sand, regular sand makes glass
During the beginning it will be important to get into ic2 not only to progress, but to ore double mainly.

To make your porcelain into bricks you will need to dry it on drying racks! Do not dry all of your porcelain though, as things like faucets need raw, not brick and should be smelted inside of the kiln.

NOTE: The kiln is a 2x2x2 multiblock where the top 2 front blocks are kiln, and the other 6 blocks are small limestone bricks to form the multiblock
No Description

By now you may be running into recipes that require diamonds so why don't we go get some to progress? First you will need something to collect some obsidian so we can get to the nether and collect some diamonds. In order to do that why don't we make a mana steel pickaxe head.

To get into multiblock crafting with immersive engineering you will need to get yourself an engineer's hammer, you can either get lucky and find one in a village or go through the torment of crafting one.

3bNow that we have gone to the nether perhaps we can make something to help with that pestering storage problem, we can start by making a storage scanner. It may not be a lot but it will help with storage until you can upgrade.
No Description
No Description
No Description

Whilst IC2 and Immersive engineering have served you well you feel like after your trip to the nether its time to advance into more RF based machinery, after starting with actually addiitons will allow you to progress foward into bigger and better things...

After your recent advancement into Actually additions you can now move foward into the depths of thermal expansion, this will allow you to make bigger and better things in the future, but what you get at present, will be a needed upgrade too
No Description

Whilst your smeltery has served you well you feel as if you need a new and better way to melt things, starting with the magma crucible for basic melting you make a magma crucible and even though your smeltery feels slow, using this to get pyrotheum would be a neat idea,

You are starting to feel alot of pain from dealing with your basic chests and drawers and feel like its time you got yourself a little storage management, whilst the storage scanner cant sort your items, it will allow you to access all the chests around your base and craft from them easily, unlike other packs we feel like even though you wont have ae2 yet, gating storage type things 1 week into the pack wasnt something we wanted to do.

The diluted pool of mana has been beneficial in your early(er) game and you feel like its time to ramp up your mana production but dont want 20diluted pools in your base, so its time to updage, just place your diluted pool and 4 buckets of glowstone into your fluid transposer and watch the pool expand its storage
Now you have yourtself a fancy storage scanner your starting to notice that your chests are filling up at an alarming rate, to fix this you look into rftools modular storage
You have decided that a central way to use your drawers would help you out a bunch along with your new storage scanner

Whilst the smeltery has served you well for all of your alloying needs its time that you changed your methods, the induction smelter wont only give you a better way to alloy your ingots, but also a way to get hardened glass to unlock some certain things...
No Description
Now that you have made yourself a new machine its time to get yourself some hardened glass, hardened glass will allow you to make the modded ore seeds from agricraft actually work

With the scarab in hand, you begin to prepare for your journey into the atum, you construct the portal out of sandstone and throw your scarab inside as sacrifice to the gods to contruct the portal before you,


If this link is not clickable take yourself to the atum wiki and it will show you the easy portal construction

https://minecraft-modsmc.fandom.com/wiki/Atum:_Journey_Into_the_Sands

Eventually there will be an ingame atum guide showing an image of this, but if its not in the akashic tome its not been implemented yet
Why don't we get started with ThaumCraft by getting the Thaumonomica and the arcane workbench to start. You can also use those scribing tools and the wood table to get a reseach table.

The quest book will have a standard progression line that you will need to follow, however there will be optional quests which will not be square in BQ that will help you along your way, but are not needed as they dont lead into other quests in order to reach the next tier.

single block fluid containers are frowned upon in this modpack, so multiblock immersive tanks are your best bet for a long time, However, energy is the opposite, as you wont get "multiblock" energy storage till rftools powercells, and actual multiblock storage with draconic so bare all this in mind

Now that you have the Workbench and the Thaumonomica you can make the crucible that can making getting vis crystals a lot easier.
The essentia smelty can make it so that you can get essentia into some Jars quickly so you can always have essentia on hand. You will also need those jars for some infusions.
Now that we have that essentia smeltry with some warding jars we can get the infusion smeltry up and running.
You can make the Thaumcraft Baubles to have some things that will help you explore easier.
The caster's gauntlet is used to activate the runic matrix and to activate infusions. Along with using foci to use caster abilities.
You are going to want to get your self some Quartz slivers to soak up those extra essences so you dont spawn anything that you dont want.

Alloying has always been an easy job, until someone took away your smeltery, to make the alloy tank work you will need a porcelain melter on either side of this, with heaters below (including the alloy tank), to melt the items into fluid, and alloy them

NOTE: you can get away with one heater for the 3 blocks if you just pick it up and move them to where the heat is needed, but it is recommended to make at least 1 more

With your advancements into thaumcraft, botania, thermal and AA made, its time to get your empowerer working, lets make the display stands to go along with the empowerer to get the ball rolling with dimension jumping somewhere other than the nether
Now that you have made it to this dimension of pure sand and hatred, it will be worth your time to find your feet here before progressing

You may have noticed that even though you are currently already quite far into actually additions you havent noticed any black quartz, thats because its been hiding away in atum out of reach, you should collect as much as you can as it will come in handy in the future

Now that you have a nether portal its time to get involved with the creatures from hell, go in get what you need and leave, or stick around if you want, but the mobs wont be happy to see you to say the least

Astral sorcery can get you alot of useful things in this modpack, whether it be faster growing plants or cave illuminators this mod is a good asset to your base, also needed to progress so i think its about time you get going

note that most of the documentation for this tier is from the astral sorcery wiki on minecraftguides.net as i do not feel confident enough to explain how it works correctly and dont want to be sending you off to the wiki every quest as that will get annoying

Now that you have explored the depths of atum, with your new knowledge of preservation and the way you can shape life into alternative things, that its time to get into the depths of blood magic, start by crafting yourself an altar, and getting yourself some snares in order to get the mobs to drop that all important will until ykou have a sentient sword, and remember, if they dont show particles you need to throw more snares

Steel creation is an intimate process that requires a little bit of time and infurstructure in order to get into, so knowing you need to cool down the ingots after they go through the blast furnace, you make an industrial chiller in order to do this.

NOTE:
item input, left of the controller
fluid input, top 
energy input to the back
and item output to the right

To make steel you need to put a quartz ingot into the blast furnace, then chill your unrefined hot steel in your chiller with a small amount of cryotheum and power

Please remember if you havent already it might be time to visit the end, as thats the only place certus will spawn

Now that the blast furnace will be used for more than just your current needs for refined iron it would be worth your time to upgrade it, you will want 2 preheaters and a new frame to go with, note that this will require power now, but the speed boost will make it more than worth your while

Although canola and steam have been good generators for power you feel the need to get an upgrade, advanced generators are mutliblocks that you can just keep adding to, however you will not be able to get EU out of this yet, that will come later

To progress further into the modpack now you have steel it will be worth making some immersive engineering multiblocks, it is recommended to make the squeezer and arc furnace, but also collect diesel from immersive petroleum

Now that you have more infrastructure its time that you make yourself some better storage to prepare yourself for the future, however you do not currently have whats needed for autocrafting, its useful to have for the mass amounts of storage

With advanced generators for your RF its about time you upgraded your EU, i recommend using the internet to find the best way to set this up if you havent used it before

the cells can be processed into plutonium which will be needed later on in the modpack so i recommend setting these up now even if not needed
Now that you have bigger machines you will want bigger crafting tables, using your recently aqquired HOP graphite you turn that into black iron in order to get your new crafters
Time to take that black iron and put it to some use, no description required
Growth essence can bring you onto bigger and better things, mainly the cloche so its about time you got onto smaller but better things, if you couldnt tell im hinting at the cloche
Like i said, the cloche
No Description
Now with ic2 at your disposal you can make yourself a metal bender, and also some presses to go with them this will alow for easier creation of gears and plates
Now you have your altar its time that you use your own body fluids to get yourself the slates you need
The addition of runes to your altar will allow you to make yourself better slates and progress further into blood magic
You feel the urge to readd some of that blood you have been draining from yourself into the altar into something more rewarding than a lesser orb you have been using in the past
Now you have yet another altar tier its time to get the next tier of slates to go with it, i know this may seem like a pain but will be worth it when you look at the things that this tier can get you

Now that you have your blood orb there will be a new type of crafting that you need to look, by filling your orb with the blood from your altar and placing it in your off hand it now has the oppertunity to be used as a form of transmution outside of the altar, to start off put your orb in your off hand and glowstone in the main to make luminessence
You will need to find yourself a collector crystal, these can be found in astral structures mostly underground and also before you set off on your travels to find one, make yourself a linking tool
crystals can be found underground around y 4, they will be needed in order to make the tool for the next quest

The Linking Tool is not just used to bind Collector Crystals to lenses, it can also be used in Iron Transmutation. Setting down some Iron ore near a Collector Crystal, you can use the Linking Tool to link the Collector Crystal to the ore. Over time this ore will change into Star Metal Ore.

8(from the astral sorcery wiki)
So now time to get the ball rolling on some atmtweak based things that actually count towards your progress, this quest unlocks the next tier

Now that you have gathered some chemicals its time that you get yourself a machine chassis to get yourself some useful enderio machines that will alloy you to make conduits easier, simple machines have been disabled as at this point, it would be stupid of you to use them
As you may already know enderio has some pretty cool machines for you to use, for now, grab yourself an alloy smelter and a sag mill to get yourself going
The enderio vat is a cool machine that allows you to turn water and 2 items into another fluid, these can be used as fuels for your generators but also other things down the road

Its that time again to learn a new mod for progression, in this tier you will be exploring mods such as alchemistry and enderio (alchemistrio, i know bad pun), but also putting a larger foothold into your magic

Now your here you may be wondering why you need to go through this mod? well turns out this mod can do alot more than what you would first think, as it can eventually turn any item into another, but for now you better get yourself the required things to get you to that point
now that you have a way to turn items into their most basic components its about time that you started combining them into bigger and better things
Using your chemicals you should make some ingots out of lithium in order to get yourself some capacitors, these are required to make enderio machines functional

With your foothold in botania reaching its potential for this world, its time to communicate with elves, make yourself a portal, this will require a bunch of terrasteel and an elite crafting table, all recipes in extended crafting will work in all bigger tables

Now that you have gotten a portal it is time to open it, you will need a decent amount of mana and once its open it will use mana for every operation that it does, so it will be useful to get mana going automatically into the pools using sparks ( or spreaders ), once open you can use this to trade with the elves and get yourself some useful things! dreamwood+elementium can be used to get yourself some better mana spreaders which will be greatly accepted for your petro petunia

Now that you are on tier 4 its time to ramp up what you need in mana requiorements, you should use the petro petunia to do so, the fuels that will work with this flower are shown in jei but note better fuels will get you more mana, with empowered oil being by far the best so it might be worth automating it
Now that you have a stable source of mana its time that you get into terrasteel crafting, remember you can use the botania book to visualise this if you dont know how it works
To make terrasteel you will need to setup your multiblock and throw a mana diamond, pearl and steel onto it and it will take half a pool of mana through the spark and make you a terrasteel
No Description

betterquesting:10.name:8: Fighting the wither the easy way
betterquesting:10.desc:8: With all those wither skeleton skulls from your new mob farm you might be looking for a new way to kill them, but this mob killer also allows you to kill the wither, which will be coming in handy very soon so get this setup as soon as you can

So far unless you are using it for power your vat has been out of action since you made that portal to communicate with the elves, its about time you got it operational again, its time to make yourself a couple buckets of vapor of levity in order to proceed within the modpack
In order to get the fusion controller you will need to get started on a few things, nether stars being the main one, if you have these automated it will be easy to get the other things you need.

Now, its about time all of that work started to pay off, to assemble the fusion controller the alchemistry guide inside of the akashic tome will be your friend, however it is just a 5x5x5 multiblock with with 3 fusion cores in the middle, and the fusion controller placed at the bottom of the 5x5 touching the middle of the bottom layer with RF fed into it, this block is very powerful because you can turn anything into anything just by additon of the 2 chemicals atomic numbers, for example 2 strontium = 1 osmium, which will be the most important recipe

Like previously mentioned in the previous quest this block will serve you best by producing osmium, you can do this by putting 1 strontium in each slot, but other chemicals also work as long as they can combine into the same atomic number, you will be glad to know this block and all of the other alchemistry machines can be automated with ae2

Now that your RF use has hit the roof and you need something more renewable, its about time you worked on some canola, make an actually additions farmer, some generators and a press to get you started, and whilst your on the subjet, get some fermenting barrels as regular oil just wont cut it.
No Description

Although you may have already made some Immersive engineering energy storage now that you have more AA you might want to stick with the theme and allow yourself to get more storage, you can make yourself portable batteries but these can be placed in world with the battery stand and can be used as energy storage for your canola generators, because power isnt something that should be wasted
Empowered blocks can be used for things like growing your own resources, im only going to ask you to make empowered enori here in order to get yourself some iron seeds

Now that you have a small break of enderio in your progression its time that you started to get the ball rolling on some better energy transfer, im guessing you already have thermal ducts so the transition should be somewhat easy

Even though by this point for your blood magic setup you will be using some kind of spawner, its about time you ramped it up, i recommend using a wither skeleton spawner as you most likely dont have that many, but will need alot more of them in the future

Now that you have osmium it is about time that you got into a new mod, Mekanica/Mekanism, using the ender crafter is simple, place ender alternators around it to initiate the crafting process, the more you have the faster the craft

Now that you have your ender crafter setup its time to put it to good use, make yourself some steel casings and use them to make all the mek machines you need, Note that when you get into mekanism cables the EU conversion rate may be a little lower than you once anticipated...

Steel casings have alot of uses, you can use them to make machines in mekanism that you will use to help you get things done easier, for example the mekanism circuits are oredict with the ic2 ones, cutting out those painful crafting recipes that we all detest, even though we play the pack for them
With the machines that i have just told you to craft, it is about time that you get going on mekanisms version of plastic, you have all the machines needed to make it, all you have to do is set it up

Now that you have unlocked mekanism its about time that you get into the types of cables they have to offer as with most things, the speeds are unmatched, please note that turning RF into EU is extremely unefficient, although it is possible i would recommend an EU port on your advanced generator

UU matter got changed in 1.6 and became a fluid, thankfully ic2classic reverts this back to the good old days of that item we all had barrels full of, dont worry you wont need that much as of now, but you might not be able to make it without a supply of scrap
HDPE, UU matter and a base full of machines its time that you switch your attention back to the arts of blood magic

The mystical forces of UU matter has obtained you the oppertunity to explore beyond earths usual exploration, the new adventures into space have opened up and its time that you took full oppertunity of it, the holo-projector is your engineers hammer and projector in one if you will, it shows you how to make the multiblock and also after all the blocks are in place, clicking the main block will form the multiblock, i haverequested the blocks you need for the multiblocks, working out which ones you need at this point is upto you
No Description

Now that you have knowledge on advanced rocketry and how you get the machines up and running this next quest will be you finding your own feet if you havent done rocketry before, i will get you some of the minimum requirements but its upto you to figure out where to go from here as its rockets as you may alreadyknow are very configurable
This altar can get you some powerful things, it isnt exactly needed at this stage but it will be nice to have and get some of the cool things it has to offer

By this point i guess that you would have a rocket built (if not what are you waiting for? check the atm expert multiblock guide for information on how to set up the rocket assembler), you will need to shift click the guidance computer inside of your rocket and insert a planet chip for luna which is aqquired by using then astrobody data processor multiblock, dont forget your space suit
On the new planet of luna, you should have a look around undeground for some out of this world crystals, enough said, get mining
Now that you have got to the planet luna its time you explored into other areas, demios will be where you want to head next to get yourself some magma cobblestone to process into planet shards

Its that part in blood magic that people either love, or they hate, but either way its going to be apart of progression, you will need to obtain all 4 types on irregular will in order to progress with different mods.

resonance of the faceted crystal will split a (regular) crystal cluster from a demon crystallizer into 1 of each other will types
gathering of the forsaken souls will grow placed crystal clusters (all types) when a mob dies - it also needs that type of will in the aura (done by putting crystals in a demon crucible)- itll use up the will in the aura but in the end you make profit
crack of the fracture crystals will break crystals in its range (without ever breaking the "source" crystal) when they grow
using a specific chemical inside of your blood altar will allow for that blood you have collected to be turned into a crystal, and that can be used to corrupt things that exsist in the world

With alchemistry added to your belt of tech mods, you have just unlocked the ability to use your advanced generators to make EU for you, so its about time you did this, you will need to craft the MV port as by this point, the LV just wont cut it
Now that we have that Pure Daisy let's make some Living rock and some Living wood. These will be needed for later on.
